1
00:00:00,733 --> 00:00:01,733
Thank you for your cooperation.

2
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,067
<i>I'm glad you can
finally go home now.</i>

3
00:00:03,133 --> 00:00:04,100
[GRUNTING]

4
00:00:04,233 --> 00:00:04,933
[GASPS]

5
00:00:05,067 --> 00:00:05,933
[SCREAMS] Ah!

6
00:00:06,067 --> 00:00:07,633
<i> Sir, how about Bok?</i>

7
00:00:07,767 --> 00:00:08,700
<i> He's dead.</i>

8
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,467
<i> Yes, I did kidnap Jade.</i>

9
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:11,567
<i> Jade.</i>

10
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:12,733
<i> But no matter what you do,</i>

11
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:15,367
<i>you can't pin your fathers'
death on me.</i>

12
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> They didn't kill each other.</i>

13
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:17,933
<i> There's someone else.</i>

14
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:19,233
<i> Sandro Soliman?</i>

15
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,267
<i>I'm afraid something might
have happened to him.</i>

16
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:24,867
<i>Are you scared that
your father might be dead?</i>

17
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,533
<i> Maybe it's time to revive</i>

18
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:30,967
<i>the annual Hotel 88
team building!</i>

19
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,233
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- [SARI SCREAMING]

20
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,033
<i>I curated today
all the activities</i>

21
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:37,467
<i>so everyone can
learn from each other.</i>

22
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,067
<i> Focus, Sari.</i>

23
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,600
<i>- Let me drive, or I'll leave!
- Then leave!</i>

24
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,733
<i>- Move! I'll drive!
- Just leave!</i>

25
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,167
<i>How can you finish
this task faster?</i>

26
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,100
<i> I'll do it.</i>

27
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,333
<i>- No, I'll do it.
- No, I'll do it.</i>

28
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,467
<i>Now you both want to do it.
What's your deal?</i>

29
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:49,967
<i>Justin, I'll do it.
I can do it. I promise.</i>

30
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:52,333
And most importantly, have fun.

31
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:54,433
- [CHEERING]
- Let's go!

32
00:00:55,467 --> 00:00:56,933
[CHEERING]

33
00:00:57,033 --> 00:00:59,233
<i> It's a tie for both teams!</i>

34
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:01,133
<i>Wait, what will we do
now, sir?</i>

35
00:01:01,267 --> 00:01:02,767
<i>Spend the whole day
bonding together,</i>

36
00:01:02,867 --> 00:01:05,400
<i>especially with people you
haven't teamed up with yet.</i>

37
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,500
<i> Seize the day!</i>

38
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:13,467
Mr. Soliman?

40
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:16,367
Sandro Soliman?

41
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:20,167
Yes. My father had a meeting
with him.

42
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,667
[LEON] So that's his name.

43
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,267
<i> Sandro.</i>

44
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:30,867
[CAFE STAFF] Sir, Mr. Soliman's
reservation was made

45
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,433
around a month ago.

46
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:34,767
Is that so?

47
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:39,000
Does your guest list say
who else they met with?

48
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:41,600
[CAFE STAFF] I'm sorry,
but we don't divulge

49
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:43,800
our guests' information.

50
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:46,800
Okay. I understand.

51
00:01:47,933 --> 00:01:49,000
Thank you.

52
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:53,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,867
[JUAN] He's from Hotel 88.

54
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,300
<i> What was he doing here?</i>

55
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:07,300
Good morning.

56
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:09,033
Are you the one
in charge of reservations?

57
00:02:09,167 --> 00:02:11,900
[CAFE STAFF] Yes, sir. Do you
want to make a reservation?

58
00:02:12,067 --> 00:02:13,500
Can you help me?

59
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,700
My father made
a reservation here

60
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,533
under Sandro Soliman.

61
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:20,267
The other guy also asked
about him earlier.

62
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:22,900
He wanted to know
who Mr. Soliman

63
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,667
was meeting that day.

64
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:28,000
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

65
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:30,500
[JUAN]<i> Why are you looking
</i> for my father?

66
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,733
<i>Are you also looking
for the treasure?</i>

67
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:45,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:41,733
[ANDY] I thought you had
a team building?

69
00:03:42,133 --> 00:03:45,500
I couldn't go there after
taking Mom to the airport.

70
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:48,100
I had some things to
take care of in Dad's business.

71
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,467
Right, right.

72
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:52,300
Frida's flight to Spain
was today.

73
00:03:52,467 --> 00:03:54,567
Is she alone or with someone?

74
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:57,033
My aunt is with her.

75
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:58,933
Alright, so let me guess.

76
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,600
You and Luna
are now in charge

77
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:03,033
of managing the businesses
Fred left behind.

78
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:04,533
That's right, Uncle.

79
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:05,867
[ANDY CHUCKLES]

80
00:04:06,167 --> 00:04:08,533
You know,
I'm not surprised that...

81
00:04:08,667 --> 00:04:12,767
you took over the businesses
your Fred left behind.

82
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:16,100
Actually, Luna's a big help.

83
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:18,500
She's the one managing
the hotel closely.

84
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:20,667
Alright, that's good.

85
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:24,133
Speaking of the hotel,
how is it? Any updates?

86
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:28,300
Well, trying to survive, Uncle.

87
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,133
Of course, it's not as popular
as your hotel right now.

88
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:34,133
No, no. I wouldn't worry
about it, you know.

89
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:35,900
Hotel 88 has just reopened.

90
00:04:36,033 --> 00:04:38,133
So just give it
some time and, uh...

91
00:04:38,533 --> 00:04:40,333
it'll pay off big for you.

92
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:46,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,133
Uncle, I just want to ask you
something.

94
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:49,300
What is it?

95
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,533
Do you know someone
named Sandro Soliman?

96
00:04:54,067 --> 00:04:55,333
Sandro Soliman...

97
00:04:55,500 --> 00:05:00,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:03,533
- Thank you, mister.
- Thank you.

99
00:05:03,733 --> 00:05:05,000
Monette, let me have a taste.

100
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:06,433
Jeez, Raphie!

101
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,333
Come on, just this once.

102
00:05:08,467 --> 00:05:09,700
Mister, two cups, please.

103
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:11,533
[MONETTE] Just take
a picture at the hotel.

104
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:12,600
We have coffee there.

105
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:14,833
Really? You won't take it out
of my pay?

106
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:16,600
[MONETTE] Seriously!

107
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:17,867
Have you seen Sari?

108
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:20,333
[MONETTE] Sari...

109
00:05:21,467 --> 00:05:23,267
- Uh... There!
- She's over there!

110
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:25,433
[MARTIN] I see.

111
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,000
Why are you looking
for her, sir?

112
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:28,167
Do you miss her already?

113
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,433
What?

114
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:31,533
I just need to double-check
something about work.

115
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,167
Is there anything
you need to do, sir?

116
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,000
- Maybe I can do--
- No.

117
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:36,567
It should be Sari.

118
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:38,933
Nevermind. You guys have fun.

119
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:45,933
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:49,067
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

121
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,867
[MONETTE] Oh, come on. Just
enjoy your coffee and chill.

122
00:05:51,967 --> 00:05:53,933
- [JUSTIN] Trixie.
- It was so tiring earlier.

123
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:06,900
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,667
Uh...

125
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:12,067
It sounds familiar.
I think, uh...

126
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,733
I think I've heard
that name before.

127
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,733
Actually, from your dad.

128
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,467
You only heard it from Dad?

129
00:06:17,633 --> 00:06:19,267
You don't know him personally?

130
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,133
[ANDY] No, no. I don't know him.

131
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:23,300
Um, I think your dad
mentioned him

132
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:25,467
while talking about one
of his business ventures

133
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:28,100
that he was going to do. Then
that name was mentioned.

134
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,833
But after that,
I didn't have any updates

135
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,767
so I didn't know if the business
pushed through or not.

136
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,633
Uh, did this Sandro guy
get in touch with you?

137
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:40,333
No, Uncle.

138
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,900
I don't know him.

139
00:06:42,867 --> 00:06:44,467
I'm just checking
Dad's business transactions,

140
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:47,667
just in case I missed something.

141
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:52,800
You know, you're such
a responsible son.

142
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,867
Anyway,

143
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:57,167
whatever business
you need to take care of,

144
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,767
I hope you can do it well.

145
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:02,433
And regarding this Soliman guy,
I hope you find him.

146
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:09,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

147
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:19,867
Jade.

148
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:29,700
[EDWARD] Jade, let's go.

149
00:07:31,167 --> 00:07:33,200
Huh? Wait, where are we going?

150
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:34,400
There's something I need
to tell you.

151
00:07:34,567 --> 00:07:36,400
Uh-- What? Edward!

152
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:43,233
You brought me here
away from everyone

153
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,533
just to tell me
your three wishes?

154
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,500
Yup.

155
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,367
Okay.

156
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:52,667
Tell me.

157
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:56,667
First, for two months...

158
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,767
you'll eat lunch with me.

159
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:02,733
Wherever you are, wherever I am,
we'll eat together.

160
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,167
Lunch?

161
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,067
Are you aware that eating lunch
with you every day

162
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,233
will ruin my schedule?

163
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,400
Okay. I thought you were serious
about making it up to me.

164
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:14,333
No, I'm serious.
I'll make it up to you.

165
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:17,000
But that doesn't mean

166
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,433
that you can control
my schedule like that.

167
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:23,300
Okay, okay.

168
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:24,700
Let's do it this way.

169
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,933
The lunch should be planned.

170
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:28,700
Is that good for you?

171
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:31,100
Fifteen days.

172
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:32,367
One month.

173
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:35,100
One month of one-hour lunches.

174
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:38,767
Exactly one hour.

175
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,200
Okay.

176
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,467
Deal.

177
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:46,933
Second.

178
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:49,467
Coffee update.

179
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:52,600
What's that?

180
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:54,300
[EDWARD] In addition to lunch,

181
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,067
we will also
have a coffee update.

182
00:08:57,633 --> 00:08:59,133
Update what?

183
00:08:59,667 --> 00:09:01,800
It can be anything.

184
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:03,067
Tss.

185
00:09:03,433 --> 00:09:05,433
Can't I just update you

186
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:07,100
while we're having lunch?

187
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,633
It's different.

188
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:11,267
Okay?

189
00:09:11,367 --> 00:09:12,267
Okay.

190
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:14,067
Fifteen days.

191
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:15,300
One month.

192
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:19,067
One month, ten minutes.

193
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:20,000
Deal.

194
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:22,133
Okay.

195
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:24,967
What's your third wish?

196
00:09:28,533 --> 00:09:29,833
Secret.

197
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,100
Hey, Edward!

198
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,000
[EDWARD] I still need
to think about it.

199
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:37,167
Bye, bye.

200
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,700
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY DARREN]

201
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:41,633
[JADE] Edward! Wait!

202
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:44,600
What is the third one?

203
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:53,800
- [MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

204
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:15,400
- [MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

205
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:30,167
[SAND CRUNCHING]

206
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:36,367
- [MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

207
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,567
[GIO] What are we?

208
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:40,367
[LUNA] We're like a bridge.

209
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,767
<i>What bridge
are you talking about?</i>

210
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:46,233
<i>- Our status right now.
- Hmm?</i>

211
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:50,100
<i>We're like at opposite ends
of a bridge.</i>

212
00:10:51,933 --> 00:10:54,033
<i> -</i> [GIGGLES]
- Just like the idiom?

213
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:56,567
<i>"We'll cross the bridge
when we get there?"</i>

214
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:57,900
[CHUCKLES]

215
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:00,100
<i> We will cross the bridge</i>

216
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:02,900
<i>when we're ready
to accept each other.</i>

217
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,767
<i> Are you ready?</i>

218
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,933
<i> For a while now.</i>

219
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,433
<i> How about you?</i>

220
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,100
<i> Are you ready?</i>

221
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:21,400
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

222
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,767
<i>- Let's dig in.
- [CHUCKLES]</i>

223
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:30,967
<i> Mm! It's hot!</i>

224
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:32,767
<i> Why?</i>

225
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,133
<i>- You're making a mess!
- [GIGGLES]</i>

226
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:38,567
<i> Watch this.</i>

227
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:40,200
<i> You have to mix it first.</i>

228
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,233
<i> Mm.</i>

229
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:45,933
<i> Mm! I said, it's hot!</i>

230
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:47,500
[GIO] Just eat slowly.

231
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:49,433
[LUNA]<i> You didn't
</i> blow on it first.

232
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:51,267
[GIO] Last bite.

233
00:11:51,367 --> 00:11:58,333
["TADHANA" BY
SOFRONIO VASQUEZ PLAYING]

234
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:20,300
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

235
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:25,467
[ART] Take the clues,
then place them on the sand.

236
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:29,333
If you turn them upside down
and then put them together,

237
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,600
you'll see that when you combine
the images of the two groups,

238
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:34,967
a big image will be formed.

239
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:43,333
[CALM MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:03,000
Hotel 88?

241
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,367
Too bad.

242
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:10,333
We would've won faster
if we looked at the other side.

243
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:12,067
Not really.

244
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:14,367
But it would be easier
to finish the tasks

245
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:18,367
if you knew exactly
what you're working towards.

246
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,800
It's not always
about finishing the job first

247
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:23,033
or getting it done.

248
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:27,233
It's how you do it
and who you do it with.

249
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,733
And that is Hotel 88.

250
00:13:29,867 --> 00:13:32,167
I hope you always remember
that Hotel 88

251
00:13:32,267 --> 00:13:34,733
isn't just about
operating a hotel.

252
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:37,867
It's also about
continuing as a family.

253
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:39,400
Justin.

254
00:13:41,533 --> 00:13:48,400
[CALM MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:52,067
- Miss Monette!
- Miss Monette.

256
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:53,833
- Yes!
- Miss Monette.

257
00:13:58,567 --> 00:14:00,567
[ART] So, everyone okay?

258
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:02,900
Here's your tentmates.

259
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:12,400
- [MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GRUNTS]

260
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:19,400
[WAVES CRASHING]

261
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:23,300
Are you really fine
with us sharing a tent?

262
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:28,367
If you're uncomfortable,
we can put this bag between us.

263
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:36,433
It's like I'm talking
to the wind.

264
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:45,167
[MUSIC TURNS SOFT]

265
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:46,467
[GRUNTS]

266
00:15:03,367 --> 00:15:10,367
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SAND CRUNCHING]

267
00:15:23,033 --> 00:15:24,500
Let's talk.

268
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:26,800
Gio...

269
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:29,500
What's the problem?
Why are you avoiding me?

270
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:31,267
We were teammates, right?

271
00:15:31,367 --> 00:15:34,167
Yeah, but you avoided me
like I'm ill or something.

272
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:36,900
Because we have nothing
to talk about.

273
00:15:37,067 --> 00:15:39,000
We have a lot to talk about.

274
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:44,900
No, we don't.

275
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,200
Luna.

276
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,067
We need to talk.

277
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:58,067
Luna...

278
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:06,400
Gio, I just want to take a rest.
Please?

279
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,400
[TENT ZIPPING]

280
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:17,400
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,900
Bro, let's just talk next time.

282
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:34,233
We have a hotel activity,

283
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,867
so I wasn't able to answer
your call.

284
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:40,100
I'll call you when I get back
to Solara island-- [SCREAMS]

285
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,700
Sari, what the hell?!

286
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,400
Sir, Monette said you were
looking for me earlier?

287
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,133
Yes, but what's that?!

288
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:48,233
Skincare, sir.

289
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:50,233
We're here at the beach all day,

290
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:53,067
so we need to take care
of our skin, sir.

291
00:16:53,067 --> 00:16:54,767
Oh, here!
I have an extra for you.

292
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:55,767
Sir, what do you want?

293
00:16:55,767 --> 00:16:57,067
- Piggy, sheep, or panda?
- I don't need it.

294
00:16:57,067 --> 00:16:59,467
[SARI] You need this, sir.
So your skin won't get

295
00:16:59,467 --> 00:17:01,067
- irritated--
- I said...

296
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:02,733
I don't need it.

297
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:05,667
Not everything
is your business, Sari.

298
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:06,967
There are boundaries.

299
00:17:07,467 --> 00:17:09,767
You're getting a bit
too comfortable.

300
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:15,133
[MARTIN] Yes,
we're at a team building.

301
00:17:15,167 --> 00:17:18,667
Yes, this is work-related,
but I hope you learn your place.

302
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:26,167
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

303
00:17:26,167 --> 00:17:27,800
I'm sorry, sir.

304
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,300
I hope you don't forget.

305
00:17:30,367 --> 00:17:32,433
I am still your boss, Sari.

306
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:41,133
- [GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

307
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,733
[SIGHS, MOUTH CLICKS]

308
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:54,200
Of course he'd get mad.

309
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:58,133
Monette, he's my boss.

310
00:17:58,133 --> 00:18:01,133
Is it wrong to think that
his skin might get irritated?

311
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,200
Sari, that was already
something personal

312
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,833
that you interfered with.

313
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:06,800
Is that a bad thing?

314
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:10,833
It's obvious you have a
happy crush on Sir Martin.

315
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,200
And there's nothing
wrong with that. It's fine.

316
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:15,533
But maybe he's
no longer comfortable

317
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:19,267
with how you show
your feelings for him.

318
00:18:21,867 --> 00:18:24,433
I only did that
because I feel inspired

319
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:26,833
working with Sir Martin.

320
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:30,733
But of course, you still have
to know your place.

321
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,733
[SIGHS]

322
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:37,767
Is that really just
a happy crush, or...

323
00:18:37,767 --> 00:18:40,867
are you hoping he'll
eventually like you back?

324
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:43,300
Oh, come on!

325
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:47,133
You know, Monette...

326
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,833
I wished to the universe
for the person...

327
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,867
...who would be my soulmate.

328
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,333
That he would come...

329
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:59,567
...on a day when the sky
is crying.

330
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:03,267
And that's Sir Martin.

331
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,233
- Oh.
- [CHUCKLES]

332
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:10,267
You know, Monette,
my parents ended up together

333
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:11,767
because of a sign.

334
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:16,233
I saw how happy they were,

335
00:19:17,133 --> 00:19:20,833
until the very last moment
of their lives.

336
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:26,267
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:19:26,267 --> 00:19:28,433
Monette, I want to experience
that too.

338
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:30,300
I want to feel...

339
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,933
what my parents had before.

340
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,233
[EXHALES]

341
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,167
And I feel like...

342
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:40,900
there's a reason
why it was Sir Martin

343
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,033
who came on that day, Monette.

344
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:47,533
So for now...

345
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,033
even if he scolded me...

346
00:19:51,133 --> 00:19:52,900
...he's still my soulmate.

347
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:56,467
Oh my.

348
00:19:56,467 --> 00:19:58,133
Must be nice.
[WHIMPERS]

349
00:19:58,133 --> 00:20:01,167
Must be nice to love
that purely.

350
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,233
- [CHUCKLES]
- That's the spirit.

351
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,033
[KIKO] There it is.

352
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,267
This is the...

353
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:09,933
Smo!--

354
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:11,933
- Smo...
- S-Smos...

355
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:13,000
[CHUCKLES]

356
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,267
Smo-- S'mores!

357
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:17,500
- It's s'mores! [CHUCKLES]
- Here.

358
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:19,333
Goodness.

359
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:22,000
It's just marshmallows
and crackers.

360
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Oh, come on! It's good.
It's actually my favorite.

361
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,000
Try it.

362
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:28,300
Come on. Let's cheers.

363
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:32,500
Cheers.

364
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:39,467
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:52,467
[EDWARD] Jade.

366
00:20:56,533 --> 00:20:57,867
Coffee update.

367
00:20:58,300 --> 00:20:59,333
Let's go.

368
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:06,967
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

369
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,300
[JADE] Really? Right now?

370
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:14,333
Coffee...

371
00:21:14,567 --> 00:21:16,000
update.

372
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:21,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

373
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:23,533
[KIKO] Just take it with you.

374
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:31,300
[JADE] Sorry, Kiko.

375
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:39,667
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

376
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:50,167
[WAVES CRASHING]

377
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,567
Hmm... It's like...

378
00:21:53,733 --> 00:21:56,433
You're stretching your neck
by looking over so much.

379
00:21:57,733 --> 00:22:01,033
You'd be a giraffe by the time
we return to the hotel.

380
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:03,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

381
00:22:03,967 --> 00:22:05,667
Are you jealous?

382
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:10,267
Me? Jealous?

383
00:22:11,233 --> 00:22:13,100
Why would I be jealous?

384
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:15,900
[SCOFFS]

385
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:18,933
Your nose is growing
just by saying that. [CHUCKLES]

386
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:21,867
No, I'm not jealous.

387
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:23,200
Jade and I are fine,

388
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:26,133
and I'm glad
that we're friends again.

389
00:22:26,633 --> 00:22:28,033
Okay.

390
00:22:28,133 --> 00:22:30,433
So, as a friend,

391
00:22:30,567 --> 00:22:34,233
you don't find it weird
that Jade went with Edward

392
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:37,633
while you're having
a moment together?

393
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:43,600
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:22:43,767 --> 00:22:46,767
Alright, then.
You're fine, as you said.

395
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:49,800
If you think about it,

396
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:54,933
it's really okay for our friends
to have boyfriends.

397
00:22:55,033 --> 00:22:56,933
Right?

398
00:22:57,033 --> 00:23:03,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

399
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,233
You're probably just hungry.

400
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:20,500
- Is this good?
- Mm-hm.

401
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:22,633
For a friend.

402
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:29,467
[MUSIC TURNS UNSETTLING]

403
00:23:29,633 --> 00:23:32,200
[LEON] I wish you had told me
everything, Dad.

404
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:35,867
<i>What really happened
that night?</i>

405
00:23:39,067 --> 00:23:41,667
<i>Why did this man
want to kill you?</i>

406
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:47,300
"Two Businessmen Killed
each other on Kaluguran Island"

407
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:51,500
<i>It had been more than a month
since Federico Almazan died.</i>

408
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:56,333
<i>It's been over 5 months since
I last spoke to my father.</i>

409
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:02,567
<i>Papa is missing
and his colleague is dead?</i>

410
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:08,400
<i>If Federico's son
is looking for you,</i>

411
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:12,333
<i>do the Almazans have something
to do with your disappearance?</i>

412
00:24:18,567 --> 00:24:21,067
<i> I need to know the truth.</i>

413
00:24:21,233 --> 00:24:24,500
<i>The Almazans will show me
where you are, Papa.</i>

414
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:34,600
<i>You don't believe that Roi
killed your fathers anymore?</i>

415
00:24:35,767 --> 00:24:36,733
<i> Do you know him?</i>

416
00:24:36,900 --> 00:24:38,200
<i> Someone is looking for him.</i>

417
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:40,600
<i> Sandro Soliman. My father.</i>

418
00:24:40,767 --> 00:24:41,767
<i> I was thrilled.</i>

419
00:24:41,900 --> 00:24:44,433
<i>We were able to get justice
for Dad 's death.</i>

420
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:47,233
<i>And we've made amends
with Kiko's family.</i>

421
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,333
- [SNAKE HISSES]
- [KIKO GROANS]

422
00:24:48,533 --> 00:24:50,567
<i>- Are you really that unlucky?
- I don't think so!</i>

423
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:52,900
<i>Every time we're together,
something bad happens!</i>

424
00:24:52,967 --> 00:24:54,867
<i>When two people meet bad luck
when they're together,</i>

425
00:24:54,967 --> 00:24:56,000
<i> it's probably a curse.</i>

426
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:58,933
<i>- Gio, put me down!
- I don't care if they hear us!</i>

427
00:24:59,067 --> 00:25:01,367
<i>Tell me, Luna.
What's going on with you?</i>

